1
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,200
Xixi.

2
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,560
Xixi! Xixi!

3
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:42,800
Xixi!

4
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:44,960
Xixi!

5
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:46,280
Xixi!

6
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,400
Where is Xixi?

7
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:52,040
You are so weird.

8
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:54,240
You didn't watch your own child,

9
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,240
and now you're asking me?

10
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:56,400
I'm warning you.

11
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:58,680
You stole the man, fine.

12
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,600
But if you dare touch my child, I will...

13
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,400
You will what?

14
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,480
You hit me again!

15
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:07,920
So what if I hit you? Do I need permission?

16
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:08,280
You...

17
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,039
Don't "you" me.

18
00:01:09,039 --> 00:01:10,280
I hit exactly who I wanted to.

19
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:11,400
You're crazy.

20
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,600
I'm perfectly sane.

21
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,840
I'm warning you.

22
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,240
You chose our rooftop as the location

23
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:16,000
because the timing is under control.

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,160
You were worried I'd call the police.

25
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,120
On the phone,

26
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,840
you told me to give you what you want voluntarily.

27
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:20,880
That means once you get what you want,

28
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:21,880
you will let it go.

29
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:23,200
You don't want to go down with me.

30
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,720
So don't push my limits.

31
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,880
Speak. What do you want?

32
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:32,170
Stop this nonsense.

33
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,280
Hand over Xixi.

34
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,600
Shut up.

35
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,840
What right do you have to talk to me like that?

36
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,640
I made so much money for you,

37
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,000
and you ruined me like this.

38
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,240
You useless man.

39
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,080
You made promises to me,

40
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,880
but you didn't keep a single one.

41
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,479
How can someone be a mistress

42
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,940
and be so self-righteous,

43
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,840
acting like a victim?

44
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,000
Shut your mouth.

45
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,640
I'm going to say it.

46
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:55,840
Chen Jian.

47
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,520
Call your mom.

48
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,240
My mom has already left.

49
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:01,840
Don't stall for time.

50
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,880
Why are you bringing parents into this?

51
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,040
Your mom didn't leave.

52
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,040
Xixi is with your mom.

53
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:06,720
What do you mean?

54
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,880
Think about it.

55
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,680
How could she kidnap Xixi?

56
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,480
Your mom conspired with her.

57
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:12,960
My mom?

58
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,600
I don't know what you're talking about.

59
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:20,240
Xixi!

60
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,079
Mommy!

61
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:22,920
Mom, is Xixi really with you?

62
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:23,720
Yes.

63
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:25,800
Don't be stupid.

64
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,040
This "Cat" told me everything.

65
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,320
Strawberry Meow Meow.

66
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:33,120
Son, your company owes so much money.

67
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,410
Even if we leave, we won't be able to pay it off in decades.

68
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:37,760
Wen Xin.

69
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:40,920
Sign this contract as the "Cat" said.

70
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,180
Strawberry Meow Meow.

71
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,400
I'll return Xixi to you.

72
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,400
Otherwise,

73
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,700
I'll throw Xixi off the building.

74
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,720
She is your granddaughter!

75
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,840
I don't care about the granddaughter.

76
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,000
Jianjian is my son.

77
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,600
I can't care about anything else.

78
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,660
I only care about Jianjian right now.

79
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,000
Hurry up and sign the contract.

80
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:57,840
Mom!

81
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,320
Or I'll jump with her.

82
00:02:59,320 --> 00:02:59,800
Don't!

83
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:01,800
Don't!

84
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,320
I'll sign. I'll sign.

85
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,520
Mom!

86
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,880
Mom!

87
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,680
Mom!

88
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,240
Mom.

89
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,880
I beg you. Please don't do this.

90
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,880
Listen to me. Would I ever hurt you?

91
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:26,440
Mom, I'm begging you. Don't.

92
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,680
Just listen to me, Jianjian.

93
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:29,840
Stop this. Don't do this.

94
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,160
Qiu Shili, hurry!

95
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,160
Mom!

96
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,480
Mom.

97
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,160
Xixi.

98
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,440
Put our child down.

99
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:36,840
Mom.

100
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,680
Stop it.

101
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,200
Tell him to put the child down.

102
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,200
Don't touch my child.

103
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,120
It's dangerous.

104
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:41,920
Don't touch my child.

105
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:42,980
Put the child down.

106
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:45,000
Tell him to put the child down. It's dangerous.

107
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,640
Let go.

108
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,320
Jianjian.

109
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:16,240
If you leave, don't ever come back.

110
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,040
Jianjian,

111
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:21,279
I only have you left now.

112
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,760
You must not let me down.

113
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,800
Mom.

114
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,130
This is my girlfriend, Wenxin.

115
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,920
We're getting married.

116
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,200
Hello, Auntie.

117
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,200
Mom.

118
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,560
Please don't go.

119
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,120
They say a man forgets his mother once he gets a wife.

120
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,380
You're not even married yet, and you already don't want me.

121
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,320
Baby.

122
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,560
Change destiny.

123
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,040
There is a price to pay.

124
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,600
Are you willing?

125
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:01,200
I am willing.

126
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:53,040
The patient's injury is in a critical area.

127
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,480
Even if he wakes up,

128
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,600
he won't be able to move.

129
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,440
Jianjian.

130
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,920
When you get better,

131
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,200
I'll take you away from here.

132
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,180
We'll go back to our hometown.

133
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,400
Don't worry.

134
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,770
I'll take care of you for the rest of your life.

135
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,120
Now that the house is sold,

136
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,320
what's your plan?

137
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:44,650
I'll find a job first

138
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,240
to support my family.

139
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,040
Right.

140
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,040
Does Wen Xin live here?

141
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,960
That's me.

142
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,600
Please sign for the package.

143
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,480
Okay. Thank you.

144
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,480
Finally,

145
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,200
it's all over.

146
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,440
Yeah.

147
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,930
Let's start over together.

148
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,970
It's nothing. Just a wiring issue.

149
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,600
I haven't received any messages

150
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,920
from twelve days later.

151
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,600
Maybe no news is good news.

152
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,600
Why haven't you changed yet?

153
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,120
Don't think just because your revolving lanterns are a hit,

154
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,120
you can act like a big shot.

155
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,400
Hurry up. We're gonna be late, man.

156
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,280
Okay.

157
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,400
Bring your new design drawings.

158
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,400
Hurry.

159
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Okay, I got it.

160
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,760
Let's go.

161
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:21,960
Let's go.

162
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:22,640
Let's go.

163
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,200
I'm sorry.

164
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,960
Our manager got held up.

165
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,240
Please wait a moment.

166
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,600
It's fine. You...

167
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,850
...go ahead.

168
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,280
No concept of time at all.

169
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,040
To think she'd keep our great designer waiting so long.

170
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:52,800
If she doesn't show up soon,

171
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,600
brother, let's play the "big shot" card and leave.

172
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,680
How big a card?

173
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,920
Two jokers and four twos?

174
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,960
You...

175
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,920
Are you the manager here?

176
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,680
Hello, my two VIP clients.

177
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:18,200
I am the investment manager here.

178
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,200
My name is Wenxin.

179
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,720
Nice to meet you both.

180
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,320
I wonder if after work,

181
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,200
I could have the honor of treating you both to dinner.

182
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:29,080
Consider it my way of making up for being late today.

183
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,640
The revolving lantern

184
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:49,170
connects to the spacetime of twelve days ago.

185
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,920
A housewife, to save her daughter,

186
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,840
teams up with a male designer from twelve days ago.

187
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,400
So, this is your story pitch?

188
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,080
Yes. What do you think?

189
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,480
I think

190
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,300
it's not great.

191
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,640
It's a wild concept,

192
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,000
but does this lantern

193
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,480
have anything to do with time?

194
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,440
Well, here's the thing.

195
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,320
The revolving lantern

196
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,840
was known as the Panchi Lamp in ancient times.

197
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:11,000
Also the Xianyin Candle, Zhuanlu Lamp, and Maqi Lamp.

198
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,360
There are many poems and legends

199
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,400
associated with it.

200
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,600
Some people also say

201
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,170
that when a person is dying,

202
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,520
scenes from their life

203
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,640
will be like a revolving lantern,

204
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,560
flashing quickly before their eyes.

205
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:22,690
That's how I came up with this concept.

206
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,160
Now that you've heard my pitch,

207
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,960
would you consider collaborating with us?

208
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:32,320
No.

209
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,840
I have other things to do. Please turn left on your way out.

210
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,640
Thank you.

211
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:45,050
Sorry to bother you.

212
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,300
What's going on? The power is out.

213
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,360
I paid the electricity bill.

214
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,560
Where is my phone?

215
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,480
How do I turn this thing on?

216
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:50,200
Wen Xin.

217
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,920
Wasn't that a story?

218
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,840
Sun Wen?

219
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,200
It's me.

220
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,280
I'm right behind you.

221
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,360
What's wrong?

222
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,620
You scared me to death.

223
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,640
Why are you here?

224
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:10,440
I live here.

225
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,840
You live here?

226
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,680
I didn't expect us to be neighbors. It's fate.

227
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,480
The manual.

228
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,960
I've been looking for it all day. Didn't expect you to have it.

229
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,890
I was just about to return it to you.

230
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,840
Did your circuit breaker trip too?

231
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,880
Yeah, the power is out here.

232
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,480
You know how to fix it, right?

233
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,320
Fix it?

234
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,640
Of course I can.

235
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:30,840
But...

236
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,200
if I fix it,

237
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,600
could you consider

238
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:36,610
investing in my design?

239
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,410
Forget it if you won't help.

240
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,520
Do me a favor.

241
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:40,440
I was joking.

242
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,640
Come to the office tomorrow.

243
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:46,480
I think this design has some merit.

244
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:47,680
Really?

245
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:48,720
I'm joking.

246
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:50,920
Then I won't fix it.

247
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:51,440
Don't you dare.
